# 🏢 Real World Scenario

## Situation

A Linux server suddenly stops accepting new files.

### Investigation

```bash
df -h
```

Output

Filesystem is 100% full.

Administrator identifies the largest directory.

```bash
sudo du -sh /*
```

Old backup files are consuming storage.

Unused backups are removed.

Disk space returns to normal.

Application starts working again.

